ATTRIBUTION REQUIREMENTS

If you redistribute this software or derivative works:
1. Include a copy of the LICENSE file (GNU AGPLv3)
2. Include this NOTICE file with all attribution notices intact
3. State any significant changes made to the original software
4. Comply with all third-party license requirements listed above

For psycopg2-binary (LGPL-3.0): You may use this library without making your
application LGPL, as long as the library is dynamically linked (not statically
embedded) and users can replace it. Source code for psycopg2 is available at
the links provided above.

For Montserrat fonts (OFL-1.1): The fonts cannot be sold by themselves but can
be bundled, embedded, or redistributed with this software. Modified versions
must use a different font name.

